<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4581576>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. The map of Taiwan and surrounding areas. (A) The location of Taiwan in East Asia. (B) The map of the major mountain ranges and the distributions of the earthworm species discussed in this paper in Taiwan. Shei- Shan Mountain Range (a), Ali-Shan Mountain Range (b), Yu-Shan Mountain Range (c), Central Mountain Range (d), and Coastal Mountain Range (e) are the five major mountain ranges in Taiwan. Earthworm species, Amynthas formosae (solid circle), Metaphire bununa (open triangle), Metaphire paiaeanna (open star), Metaphire yuanpoaea (open circle), Metaphire nanaoensis (open square), Metaphire taiaeanensis (solid triangle), and Metaphire tahanmonta (solid star), showed different distributions in Taiwan." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4581576/files/figure.png" .

